project.description: Wardha district (Marathi: वर्धा जिल्हा) is one of the 36 districts in Maharashtra state in western India. This district is a part of Nagpur Division. The city of Wardha is the administrative headquarters of the district. The district had a population of 1,300,774 of which 73.72% were rural in 1376 villages as of census 2011.
